    • Good evening, Customer Service Team, My name is Brian Serratelli, and I am a firefighter with the Granbury Volunteer Fire Department. I recently purchased the Carbonic Blaze Smart Watch (Sport Mode - Rugged) via Amazon and received it this afternoon. I was excited to find a watch that seemed perfect for my demanding duties as a firefighter, designed to handle rugged conditions without concern for damage. Unfortunately, this evening, while preparing for a structure fire, the watch band broke, causing the watch to fall to the floor. This was both surprising and disappointing, as I had high expectations for the durability and toughness advertised for this product. Prior to this incident, I had been enthusiastically sharing with my colleagues at the firehouse how impressive the watch was.       Pretty great watch. I didn't have much trouble pairing it with my phone. It asks you to change a setting in your phone to high power consumption, which I don't really like, it's optional but it isn't obvious that you can skip the step.
      Most of the apps seem to work very well, the only app that I had an issue with is the blood pressure app. The watch has 3 lasers on the bottom of the watch, which I guess are used to take your pulse. However my blood pressure read really high, I wasn't particularly stressed that day or doing any strenuous activities so I don't know why I read so high. My blood pressure is normal very good so I'm surprised it read so high.
      The other issue I had with is the app loading animations are choppy. It's not a big deal, I just thought I $160+ watch would have smooth animations. Since this is my first smart watch I don't know if other watches at this price point have smoother animations or if all watches are just like that.

      I really want to like this watch as I was looking for a no frills, "fitness watch" that would help in tracking some workouts.
